# nl-rag distilled facts — domain: 1st-british-academy-film-awards
# one declarative sentence per line; load with:  neuron --db app.db import pack.facts --scope knowledge
[src:1st-british-academy-film-awards/10th-british-academy-film-awards] The **10th British Academy Film Awards**, given by the British Academy of Film and Television Arts in 1957, honoured the best films of 1956.
[src:1st-british-academy-film-awards/11th-british-academy-film-awards] The **11th British Academy Film Awards**, given by the British Academy of Film and Television Arts, were held on 6 March 1958, to honor the best national and foreign films of 1957.
[src:1st-british-academy-film-awards/12th-british-academy-film-awards] The **12th British Academy Film Awards**, given by the British Academy of Film and Television Arts in 1959, honoured the best films of 1958.
[src:1st-british-academy-film-awards/18th-british-academy-film-awards] The **18th British Academy Film Awards**, given by the British Academy of Film and Television Arts in 1965, honoured the best films of 1964.
[src:1st-british-academy-film-awards/1947-in-film] The year **1947 in film** involved some significant events.
[src:1st-british-academy-film-awards/1948-in-film] The year **1948 in film** involved some significant events.
[src:1st-british-academy-film-awards/19th-british-academy-film-awards] The **19th British Academy Film Awards**, given by the British Academy of Film and Television Arts in 1966, honoured the best films of 1965.
[src:1st-british-academy-film-awards/1st-british-academy-film-awards] The **1st British Film Academy Awards** (retroactively known as the British Academy Film Awards), were handed out on 29 May 1949 at the Odeon Luxe Leicester Square, in London, for films shown in the United Kingdom in 1947 and 1948.
[src:1st-british-academy-film-awards/1st-british-academy-film-awards] They were presented by the British Film Academy (currently, British Academy of Film and Television Arts (BAFTA)), an organisation established in 1947 by filmmakers from Great Britain, for the "advancement of the art and technique of the film".
[src:1st-british-academy-film-awards/1st-british-academy-film-awards] The Academy bestowed accolades in three categories: Best British Film, Best Picture from any source – British or Foreign and a Special Award.
[src:1st-british-academy-film-awards/1st-british-academy-film-awards] British film producer Michael Balcon chaired the ceremony.
[src:1st-british-academy-film-awards/1st-british-academy-film-awards] All sources used in this article make no mention of nominees in any of the categories.
